    {
      "id": "principles-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 80,
      "y": 1320,
      "width": 1120,
      "height": 60,
      "text": "1. Start simple (single agent + tools), add complexity only when it demonstrably improves outcomes\n2. Invest more in tool design than agent orchestration -- tools give ground truth, not LLM opinions\n3. Workflows (deterministic code paths) before agents (dynamic LLM-driven control)\n4. Cross-model evaluation: GPT generates, Claude evaluates (different blind spots)",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#5c5f66",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
